<main>

  <div class="support-container">
    <section class="support-hero">
      <div class="support-eyebrow">Support</div>
      <h1 class="support-title">Sustain the Practice</h1>
      <p class="support-description">This practice has been alive for thirty years. It runs on patience, materials, daily hours, and the belief that discarded things matter. There is no institution behind it. There is a person in Saint Paul making work every day. Your support keeps the daily practice alive.</p>
      <div class="quick-actions">
        <a href="#tiers" class="quick-link">Subscribe</a>
        <a href="#contribute" class="quick-link">Contribute</a>
        <a href="#circle" class="quick-link">The Circle</a>
        <a href="#ways" class="quick-link">Other Ways</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="support-wide">
    <section class="tiers-section reveal" id="tiers">
      <div class="section-label">Engagement</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Three Ways In</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">The practice does not ask for patrons. It asks for companions. Each tier is a different kind of presence.</p>
      <div class="tier-grid">
        <div class="tier-card reveal">
          <div class="tier-name">The Reader</div>
          <div class="tier-price">Free</div>
          <div class="tier-desc">Subscribe to dispatches. Receive the work as it arrives. The writing, the methodology, the fragments. No paywall. The Reader is the first circle — the one who shows up because the words asked them to.</div>
          <a href="#" class="tier-cta">Subscribe</a>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-card tier-featured reveal">
          <div class="tier-name">The Sustainer</div>
          <div class="tier-price">Monthly</div>
          <div class="tier-desc">Keep the daily practice alive. A monthly contribution that covers materials, time, and the unsexy infrastructure that lets an independent practice continue. Named in the archive. Receives work before it publishes.</div>
          <div class="tier-benefits">
            <div class="tier-benefit">Early access to new pieces</div>
            <div class="tier-benefit">Named in the Oyparaploo archive</div>
            <div class="tier-benefit">Methodology notes as they develop</div>
          </div>
          <a href="#" class="tier-cta">Sustain</a>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-card reveal">
          <div class="tier-name">The Companion</div>
          <div class="tier-price">Yearly</div>
          <div class="tier-desc">Full access to the methodology. The 70 shaping prompts, the rotation prompts, the living documents. Named in the colophon. The Companion walks alongside the practice as it grows.</div>
          <div class="tier-benefits">
            <div class="tier-benefit">Everything in The Sustainer</div>
            <div class="tier-benefit">Full methodology access</div>
            <div class="tier-benefit">Named in the site colophon</div>
            <div class="tier-benefit">Annual letter from the elder</div>
          </div>
          <a href="#" class="tier-cta">Companion</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="circle-section reveal" id="circle">
    <div class="circle-inner">
      <div class="section-label" style="color:#b5ada5;">The inner ring</div>
      <h2 class="circle-title">The Circle</h2>
      <p class="circle-intro">The practice figures — Mercy Momo, Bomu, the animal circle — have companions in the world too. The Circle is for those who want a direct relationship with the work. Not an audience. A presence.</p>
      <div class="circle-grid">
        <a href="#" class="circle-card"><div class="circle-card-name">Commission</div><div class="circle-card-desc">A piece made for a specific occasion, person, or place. Shaped using the full methodology. The elder decides what form it takes. The commissioner decides what it is for.</div></a>
        <a href="#" class="circle-card"><div class="circle-card-name">Host</div><div class="circle-card-desc">Bring the practice to a place. A reading, a workshop, a residency. The practice travels with its tools and leaves something behind that was not there before.</div></a>
        <a href="#" class="circle-card"><div class="circle-card-name">Collaborate</div><div class="circle-card-desc">Work alongside the practice on a specific project. The collaborator must push back. Must hold the line. Must tell the truth about what is alive and what is dead.</div></a>
        <a href="#" class="circle-card"><div class="circle-card-name">Legacy</div><div class="circle-card-desc">Sustain the practice beyond a single lifetime. Ensure the archive, the methodology, and the 140,000 files outlive the hands that made them.</div></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="support-container">
    <section class="contribute-section reveal" id="contribute">
      <div class="contribute-card">
        <h2 class="contribute-title">Contribute</h2>
        <p class="contribute-desc">Every contribution, any size, goes directly to the daily practice. Materials. Time. The unglamorous work of keeping an independent creative practice alive in the Twin Cities.</p>
        <div class="amount-row">
          <button class="amount-pill" onclick="selectAmount(this)">$10</button>
          <button class="amount-pill" onclick="selectAmount(this)">$25</button>
          <button class="amount-pill active" onclick="selectAmount(this)">$50</button>
          <button class="amount-pill" onclick="selectAmount(this)">$100</button>
          <button class="amount-pill" onclick="selectAmount(this)">$250</button>
          <button class="amount-pill" onclick="selectAmount(this)">Other</button>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="contribute-cta">Contribute Now</a>
        <p class="contribute-note">Oyparaploo is an independent practice. Minneapolis ~ Saint Paul.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="support-wide">
    <section class="ways-section reveal" id="ways">
      <div class="section-label">Other ways</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Support Without Money</h2>
      <div class="ways-grid">
        <a href="#" class="way-card"><div class="way-title">Share the Work</div><div class="way-desc">Send a piece to someone who needs it. The writing was made to travel. A link, a reading aloud, a passage copied into a letter. The share is the oldest form of support.</div><span class="way-arrow">&#8594;</span></a>
        <a href="#" class="way-card"><div class="way-title">Teach With It</div><div class="way-desc">Use the methodology in your own practice. The 70 prompts, the shaping tools, the categories. Bring them into a classroom, a workshop, a kitchen table. The tools want to be used.</div><span class="way-arrow">&#8594;</span></a>
        <a href="#" class="way-card"><div class="way-title">Witness</div><div class="way-desc">Read. Come back. Read again. The witness who returns is doing the most important work. The practice does not need applause. It needs someone who was there and came back.</div><span class="way-arrow">&#8594;</span></a>
        <a href="#" class="way-card"><div class="way-title">Tell Us</div><div class="way-desc">If a piece changed something. If a phrase stopped you. If you used a prompt and it worked. The practice needs to know it landed. One sentence is enough.</div><span class="way-arrow">&#8594;</span></a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

